 # mini-crawler (compose) — updated: OpenAI + robots.txt + token caps
 
 Minimal end-to-end crawl → ingest → infer → serve loop runnable with Docker Compose.
 
 What this repo contains
 - api: FastAPI service that accepts job enqueues and serves results (also serves test fixtures)
 - worker: single worker process combining crawling, ingest, dedupe, model call, DB writes
 - control: small FastAPI service to toggle 3 kill-switch flags in Redis
 - redis: queue + flag store
 - SQLite at ./data/data.db (created by the API on startup)
 - tests/fixtures: three static pages used by the smoke test
 - tests/smoke_test.py: single end-to-end smoke that CI runs
 
 Quick start (local)
 1. Copy .env.example -> .env and edit if you want OpenAI integration:
    cp .env.example .env
    # set MODEL_PROVIDER=openai and MODEL_API_KEY if you want to enable OpenAI
 2. Build & start:
    docker compose build --no-cache
    docker compose up -d
 3. Enqueue a job:
    curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/jobs" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -d '{"start_url":"http://host.docker.internal:8000/tests/fixtures/page1.html","max_pages":3}'
 4. Check job:
    curl http://localhost:8000/jobs/<job_id>
 
 Kill-switches (toggle)
 - Pause new jobs:
   curl -X POST http://localhost:9000/toggle -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"pause_jobs":true}'
 - Disable model calls:
   curl -X POST http://localhost:9000/toggle -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"disable_model":true}'
 - Freeze writes:
   curl -X POST http://localhost:9000/toggle -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"read_only_db":true}'
 
 Safety & caps
 - Per-job max pages enforced and clamped (default <= 3)
 - Per-day model token cap enforced via Redis key model:tokens:YYYYMMDD
 - If MODEL_API_KEY is not set the worker uses a deterministic local summarizer by default
 - Control service exposes /tokens to view today's token usage
 
 Tests
 - Run smoke tests locally:
   pytest -q tests/smoke_test.py
 - CI runs the same smoke test on every push (see .github/workflows/ci.yml)
 
 Developer notes
 - Worker implements robots.txt best-effort caching (1 hour) in Redis
 - Token estimation uses tiktoken if installed, otherwise a heuristic (1 token ~ 4 chars)
 
